However, I also recognize that mistakes can be valuable learning experiences, and I am willing to take the time to reflect on them and improve my skills.\n\nIn terms of doubting my overall abilities and knowledge, I tend to be more self-critical than most, and I may overanalyze minor mistakes or setbacks. 7 - Strongly Agree

As an ISTP, I value practicality and efficiency in my work and personal life. While I understand the importance of accuracy and attention to detail, I tend to focus on finding solutions and moving forward rather than dwelling on mistakes or perceived shortcomings. However, I also recognize that mistakes can be valuable learning experiences, and I am willing to take the time to reflect on them and improve my skills.

In terms of doubting my overall abilities and knowledge, I tend to be more self-critical than most, and I may overanalyze minor mistakes or setbacks. However, I also recognize that these doubts are a natural part of the learning process, and I am willing to work through them in order to improve and grow.
